ossible radiative processes can be ruled out for the X-ray flares\ncreation. Our X-ray flaring rate is consistent with those observed in the 2012\nChandra XVP campaign. No increase in the flaring activity was thus triggered\nclose to the DSO/G2 pericenter passage. Moreover, higher X-ray flaring rates\nhad already been observed with no increase in the quiescent level. There is\nthus no direct link between an X-ray flaring-rate increase and an\naccretion-rate change. (abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Mar 2016 10:26:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-04-27"}
